-> Added security dependencies like spring-boot-starter-security, jjwt and spring-boot-starter-web.

-> Created JwtUtil class in com.example.bookstoreapi.security package which handles JWT creation and validation.

-> Created a SecurityConfig class in package com.example.bookstoreapi.config.

-> Created a JwtRequestFilter which extends to OncePerRequestFilter in package com.example.bookstoreapi.security.

-> In the com.example.bookstoreapi.controller package added AuthController class.

-> Created WebConfig class which implements WebMvcConfigurer in package com.example.bookstoreapi.config which is used to handle CORS.

-> Using all the above classes and functions in them the RESTful Services are now secured with JWD-based authentication.
